\begin_layout Standard
During undergraduate studies in Petroleum Engineering,
 students often face difficulties in organizing their academic journey,
 particularly due to the complexity of the curriculum,
 mandatory workload requirements,
 extracurricular activities,
 and the Final Graduation Project.
 The lack of a structured plan can lead to delayed graduation,
 increased stress,
 and reduced academic performance.
 To address this issue,
 this project proposes the development of PetroPlanner,
 an interactive software tool designed to assist engineering students in managing their academic schedules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The system will enable the simulation of various course planning scenarios across semesters,
 taking into account factors such as average course approval rates,
 the impact of postponing subjects,
 recommended weekly workload,
 and GPA progression.
 Additionally,
 PetroPlanner will include features to monitor internship activities,
 complementary academic requirements,
 and individual progress in relation to the curriculum.
 The methodology involves applying object-oriented analysis and modeling techniques,
 including the creation of class diagrams,
 use cases,
 and prototypes.
 The system will be developed using C++23 with a graphical user interface built in Qt 6.6 and will utilize SQLite as the local database,
 along with auxiliary libraries for generating statistical graphs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Through development,
 testing,
 and simulations,
 the effectiveness of the tool in helping students organize and optimize their academic planning is expected to be validated.
 PetroPlanner’s main advantage lies in its customization for the specific context of Petroleum Engineering,
 adapting to the real demands of students and institutional requirements.
 As a result,
 the system aims to reduce the burden of individual planning,
 support strategic decision-making,
 and contribute to a more efficient and successful academic path.
